chapter is a merry end to mirth when the young girls were left alone they leaned two by two on the window sills chatting craning out their heads and talking from one window to the other
they saw the young men emerge from the cafe bombard a seminar m
the latter turned round made signs to them smiled and disappeared in that dusty sunday throng which makes a weekly invasion into the champs elysees
