it will be a lesson to the bonapartist s
it was thus that the phantom which had been called m
madeleine vanished from m
shrm
only three or four persons in all the town remained faithful to his memory
the old port read who had served him was among the number
on the evening of that day the worthy old woman was sitting in her lodge still in a thorough bright and absorbed in sad reflections
the factory had been closed all day the carriage gate was bolted the street was deserted
there was no one in the house but the two guns sister per le tue and sister simply ce who were watching beside the body of fantine
towards the hour when m
madeleine was accustomed to return home the good port red cross mechanically took from a drawer the key of m
then she sat down again on her chair and became absorbed in thought once more
the poor good old woman had done all this without being conscious of it
it was only at the expiration of two hours that she roused herself from here every and exclaimed hold
my good god jesus
and i hung his key on the nail
at that moment the small window in the lodge opened a hand passed through seized the key and the candlestick and lighted the taper at the candle which was burning there
the port read raises her eyes and stood there with gaping mouth and a shriek which she confined to her throat
she knew that hand that arm the sleeve of that cost
