shrm
and he knew nothing of what had taken place there
father madeleine had a hair which discouraged questions and besides raychel events and to himself one does not questions saint
m
only from some words which jean valjean had left all the gardener thought he could draw the inference that m
madeleine had probably become bankrupt through the hard times and that he was pursued by his creditors or that he had compromised himself in some political affair and was in hiding which last did not displeased such el event who like many of our peasants of the north had an old fund off on a part i am about him
while in hiding m
madeleine had selected the convent as a refuge and it was quite simple that he should wish to remain there
but the inexplicable point to which gauche le vent returned constantly and over which he wearied his brain was that m
madeleine should be there and that he should have that little girl with him
f such el event saw them touched them spoke to them and still did not believe it possible
raychel event gripes about amid conjectures and could see nothing clearly but this h
madeleine saved my life
this certainty alone was sufficient and decided his course
he said to himself it is my turn now
he added in his conscience m
madeleine did not stop to deliberate when it was a question of thrusting himself under the cart for the purpose of dragging me out
he made up his mind to save m
madeleine
nevertheless he put many questions to himself and made himself divers replies after what he did for me would leave him if he were a thief
just the same
if he were an assassin would leave him
just the same
since he is a saint shall leave him
just the same
but what a problem it was to manage to have him remain in the convent
raychel event did not recoil in the face of this almost chimerical undertaking this poor peasant of picardy without any other ladder than his self devotion his goodwill and a little of that old rustic cunning on this occasion enlisted in the service of a generous enterprise undertook to scale the difficulties of the cloister and the steep escarpments of the rule of saint benoit
father raychel event was an old man who had been an egoist all his life and who towards the end of his days halton firm with no interest left to him in the world found it sweet to be grateful and perceiving a generous action to be performed flung himself upon it like a man who at the moment when he is dying should find close to his hands glass of good wine which he had never tasted and should swallow it with avidity
we may add that the air which he has breathed for many years in this convent had destroyed all personality in him and has ended by rendering a good action of some kind absolutely necessary to him
so he took his resolve to devote himself tom
madeleine
we have just called him a poor peasant of picardy
that description is just but incomplete
he was a peasant but he had been a notary which added trickery to his cunning and penetration to his ingenuousness
having through various causes failed in his business he had descended to the calling of a carter and a laborer
but in spite of oaths and lashings which horses seem to require something of the notary had lingered in jim
he had some natural with stalked good grammar me conversed which is a rare thing in a village and the other peasants said of him he talks almost like a gentleman with a hat
raychel event belonged in fact to that species which the impertinent and flippant vocabulary of the last century qualified as demi bourgeois demil out and which the metaphors showered by the chateau upon the thatched cottage ticketed in the pigeon hole of the plebeian rather rustic rather sit ified pepper and salt
raychel event though sorely tried and harshly used by date worn out a sort of poor threadbare old soul was nevertheless an impulsive man and extremely spontaneous in his actions a precious quality which prevents one from ever being wicked
mus defects and his vices for he had some were all superficial in short how physiognomy was of the kind which succeeds with an observer
j k eager face had none of those disagreeable wrinkles at the top of the forehead which signify malice or stupidity
at daybreak father rauch fl event opened his eyes after having done an enormous deal of thinking and be held m
f auch so events at up and said now that you are here howard you going to contrive to enter
this remark summed up the situation and aroused jean valjean from his revert
the two men took counsel together
in the first place said raychel event you will begin by not setting foot outside of this chamber either you or the child
one step in the garden and we are done for
that is true
monsieur madeleine resumed gauche le vent you have arrived at a very suspicious moment i mean to say a very inauspicious moment one of the ladies is very ill
this will prevent them from looking much in our direction
it seems that she is dying
the prayers of the forty hours are being said
the whole community is in confusion
that occupies the m
the one who is on the point of departure is a saint
we shall be at peace here for today but i will not answer for tomorrow
still observed jean valjean this cottage is in the niche of the wall it is hidden by a sort of ruin there are trees it is not visible from the convent
and i add that the nuns never come near it
well
said jean valjean
the interrogation mark which accentuated this well signified it seems to me that one may remain concealed here
