raychel event recoiled and cracked his finger joints
but that is impossible
nah
impossible to take a hammer and drive some nails in a plank
what seemed unprecedented today fuel events as we repeat a simple matter to jean valjean
jean valjean had been in worse straits than this
any man who has been a prisoner understands how to contract himself to hit the diameter of the escape
the prisoner is subject to flight as the sick man is subject to a crisis which saves or kills him
an escape is a cure
what does not a man undergo for the sake of a cure
if we are to credit the monk austin castillejo this was the means employed by charles the fifth desirous of seeing the plumbed for the last time after his abdication
he had her brought into and carried out of the monastery of saint yuste in this manner
faith el event who had recovered himself a little exclaimed but how will you manage to breathe
i will breathe
in that box
the mere thought of it suffocates me
you surely must have a gimlet you will make a few holes here and there around my mouth and you will nail the top plank on loosely
good
and what if you should happen to cough or to sneeze
a man who is making his escape does not count or sneeze
and jean valjean added father raychel event we must come to a decision i must either be caught here or accept this escape through the hearse
everyone has noticed the taste which cats have for pausing and lounging between the two leaves of a half shut door
who is there who has not said to a cat do come in
there are men who when an incident stands half open before them have the same tendency to halt in inc ecision between two resolutions at the risk of getting crushed through the abrupt closing of the adventure by date
the over prudent cats as they are and because they are cats sometimes incur more danger than the audacious
faux nel event was of this hesitating nature
he grumbled well since there is no other means
jean valjean resumed the only thing which troubles me is what will take place at the cemetery
that is the very point that is not troublesome exclaimed gauche le vent
if you are sure of coming out of the coffin all right i am sure of getting you out of the grave
the grave digger is a drunkard and a friend of mine
he is rather me etienne
an old fellow of the old school
the grave digger puts the corpses in the grave and i put the grave digger in my pocket
i will tell you what will take place
they will arrive a little before dusk three quarters of an hour before the gates of the cemetery are closed
the near we will drive directly up to the grave
i shall follow that is my business
i shall have a hammer a chisel and some pincers in my pocket
the priest says the prayers makes the sign of the cross sprinkles the holy water and takes his departure
i am left alone with father me etienne
he is my friend i tell you
one of two things will happen he will either be sober or he will not be sober
then you have no longer anyone but me to deal with
jean valjean held out his hand and caucus i event precipitated himself upon it with the touching effusion of a peasant
that is settled father raychel event
all will go well
provided nothing goes wrong thought raychel event
in that case it would be terrible
chapter v it is not necessary to be drunk in order to be immortal on the following day as the sun was declining the very rare passersby on the boulevard du maine pulled off their hats to an old fashioned hearse ornamented with skills cross bones and tears
this hearse contained a coffin covered with a white cloth over which spread a large black cross like a huge corpse with dropping arms
a mourning coach in which could be seen a priest in his surplice and a choirboy in his red cap followed
behind it came an old man in the garments of a laborer who lim pedaling
the procession was going in the direction of the vaugirard cemetery
the vaugirard cemetery formed an exception among the cemeteries of paris
it had its peculiar usages just as it had its carriage entrance and its house door which old people in the quarter who cling tenaciously to ancient words still called the ports cavaliers and the ports pie tonne
the bernard j new benedictines of the rue petit pico y z had obtained permission as we have already stated to be buried there in a corner apart and at night the plot of land having formerly belonged to their community
the gravediggers being thus bound to service in the evening in summer and at night in winter in this cemetery they were subjected to a special discipline
the gates of the paris cemeteries closed at that epoch at sundown and this being a municipal regulation the va unitard cemetery was bound by it like the rest
the carriage rare and the house door were two contiguous r rated gates adjoining a pavilion built by the architect petronet and inhabited by the door keeper of the cemetery
these gates therefore swung inexorably on their hinges at the instant when the sun disappeared behind the dome of the invalides
the grave digger dropped his card into this box the porter heard it fall pulled the food and the small door opened
if the man had not miss and he mentioned his name the porter who was sometimes in bed and asleep rose came out and identified the man and opened the gate with his key the grave digger stepped out but had to pay a fine if fifteen france
this cemetery with its peculiarities outside the regulations embarrassed the symmetry of the administration
it was suppressed a little later than
the vaugirard cemetery was what may be called a faded cemetery
it was falling into disuse
dampness was invading of the flowers were deserting it
the bourgeois did not care much about being buried in the vaugirard it hinted at poverty
pere lachaise if you please
to be buried in pere lachaise is equivalent to having furniture of mahogany
it is recognized as elegant
the vaugirard cemetery was a venerable enclosure planted like an old fashioned french garden
straight alleys box thuya trees holly ancient tombs beneath aged cypress trees and very tall grass
in the evening it was tragic there
there were very lugubrious lines about it
the sun had not yet set when the hearse with the white pali and the black cross entered the avenue of the vaugirard cemetery
the lame man who followed it was no other than gauche levert
the interment of mother crucifixion in the vault under the altar the editor cosette the introduction of jean valjean to the dead room all had been executed without difficulty and there had been to hitch
let us remark in passing that the burial of mother crucifixion under the altar of the convent is a perfectly denial offence in our sight
it is one of the faults which resemble a duty
the nuns had committed it not only without difficulty but even with the applause of their own consciences
in the cloister what is called the government is only an inter meddling with authority an interference which is always questionable
in the first place the rule as for the code we shall see
make as many laws as you please men but keep them for yourselves
the tribute to caesar is never anything but the remnants of the tribute to god
a prince is nothing in the presence of a principle
raychel event limped along behind the head as in a very spm tented trans of mind
his twin plots the one with the nuns the one for the convent the other against it the other with m
madeleine had succeeded to all appearance
raychel event no longer felt doubtful as to his success
what remained to be done was a mere nothing
within the last two years he had made good father me etienne a chubby cheeked person drunk at least ten times
he played with father me etienne
he did what he liked with him
he made him dance according to his whom
all at once the headset alter it had reached the gate
the permission for interment must be exhibited
during this colloquy which always is productive of a delay or from one to two minutes someone a stranger came and placed himself behind the hearse beside raychel event
he was a sort of laboring man who wore a waistcoat with large pockets and carried a mattock under his arm
raychel event surveyed this stranger
who are you
he demanded
the man replied the grave digger
if a man could survive the flow of a cannonball fill in the breast he would make the same face that caucus le vent made
the grave digger
yes
you
i
father me etienne is the grave digger
he was
what
he was
he is dead
raychel event had expected anything but this that a grave digger could die
it is true nevertheless that gravediggers dodie themselves
raychel event stood there with his mouth wide open
he had hardly the strength to stammer but it is not possible
it is so
but he persisted feebly father me etienne is the grave digger
after napoleon louis xviii
after me etienne try bier
peasant my name is bribie r
raychel event who was deadly pale stared at this fri view
he was at all think i did utterly funereal man
he had the air of an unsuccessful doctor who had turned grave digger
faucheur vent burst out laughing
ah
said he whats user things do happen
