the porter raised his head and said are you a police spy air
marius went off quite abashed but delighted
he was getting on
on the following day m
leblanc and his daughter made only a very brief stay in the luxembourg they went away while it was still broad daylight
on arriving at the carriage entrance m
leblanc made his daughter pass in first then paused before crossing the threshold and stared intently at marius
on the next day they did not come to the luxembourg
marius waited for them all day in vain
he walked about beneath the windows until the light was extinguished
the next day no one at the luxembourg
marius waited all day then went and did sentinel duty under their windows
his dinner took care of itself
fever nourishes the sick man and love the liver
he spent a week in this manner
m
leblanc no longer appeared at the luxembourg
marius indulged in melancholy conjecture she dared not watch the ports cochere during the day he contented himself with going at night to gaze upon the red light of the windows
at times he saw shadows foot across them and his heart began to beat
on the eighth day when he arrived under the windows there was no light in them
hello
he said the lamp is not lighted yet
but it is dark
can they have gone out
until midnight
until one in the morning
not a light appeared in the windows of the third story and no one entered the house
he went away in a very gloomy frame of mind
on the morrow to the only existed from morrow tomorrow there was so to speak no today for him on the morrow he found no one at the luxembourg he had expected this
