at the top of the rue petit gentilly he turned to the left and proceeded rapidly to the rue du petit ban quiet
the day was declining the snow which had ceased for a moment had just begun again
marius posted himself on the watch at the very corner of the rue du petit ban quiet which was deserted as usual and did not follow jon frette into it
it was lucky that he did so for on arriving in the vicinity of the wall where marius had heard the long haired man and the bearded man conversing monde et he turned round made sure that no one was following him did not see him then sprang across the wall and disappeared
the wasteland bordered by this wall communicated with the backyard of an ec livery stable keeper of bad repute who had failed and who still kept a few old single seater berlins under his sheds
marius had given his key to the inspector of police it was important therefore that he should make haste
evening had arrived night had almost closed in on the horizon and in the immensity of space there remained but one spot illuminated by the sun and that was the moon
it was rising in a ruddy flow behind the low some of salpetriere
marius returned to no
with great strides
the door was still open when he arrived
he mounted the stairs on tiptoe and glided along the wall of the corridor to his chamber
this corridor as the reader will remember was bordered on both sides by attics all of which were for the moment empty and to let
as he passed one of these attics marius though the perceived in the uninhabited sell the motionless heads of four men vaguely lighted up by a remnant of daylight falling through a dormer window
marius made no attempt to see not wishing to be seen himself
he succeeded in reaching his chamber without being seen and without making any noise
it was high time
chapter xvi in which will be found the words to an english air which was in fashion in marius seated himself on his bed
only half an hour separated him from what was about to happen
he heard the beating of his arteries as one hears the ticking of a watch in the dark
he thought of the double march which was going on at that moment in the dark crime advancing on one side justice coming up on the other
he was not afraid but he could not think without a shudder of what was about to take place
as is the case with all those who are suddenly assailed by an unforeseen adventure the entire day produced upon him the effect of a dream and in order to persuade himself that he was not the prey of a nightmare he had to feel the cold barrels of the steel pistols in his trousers pockets
it was no longer showing the moon disengaged itself more and more clearly from the mist and its light mingled with the white reflection of the snow which had fallen communicated to the chamber a sort of twilight aspect
there was a light in the job fretted en
marius saw the hole in the wall shining with a reddish glow which seemed bloody to tim
it was true that the light could not be produced by a candle
however there was not a sound in the jon dee the quarters not a soul was moving there not a soul speaking not a breath the silence was glacial and profound and had it not been for that light he might have thought himself next door to a sepulchre
marius softly removed his boots and pushed them under his bed
several minutes elapsed
