either by chance or because he had begun to feel a dawning uneasiness n
there were now four men three seated on the be done standing near the door post all four with bare arms and motionless with faces smeared with black
one of those on the bed was leaning against the wall with closed eyes and it might have been supposed that he was asleep
he was old his white hair contrasting with his blackened face produced a horrible effect
the other two seemed to be young one wore a beard the other wore his hair long
none of them had on shoes those who did not wear socks were barefooted
jon dee the noticed that m
they are friends
they are neighbors said he
their faces are black because they work in charcoal
they are chimney builders
have pity on my misery
i will not ask you much for it
how much do you think it is worth
well said m
leblanc looking jon dee the full in the eye and with the manner of a man who is on his guard it is done signboard for a tavern and is worth about three craggs
jon dee the replied sweetly have you your pocketbook with you
i should be satisfied with a thousand crowns
m
leblanc sprang up placed his back against the wall and cast a rapid glance around the room
he had jon dee the on his left on the side near the window and the yonder the woman and the four men on his right on the side near the door
the four men did not stir and did not even seem to be looking on
jon dee the bad again begun to speak in a plaintive tone with so vague an eye and so lamentable an intimation that m
leblanc might have supposed that what he had before him was a man who had simply gone mad with misery
