that did amuse me
he was out of breath
his little narrow chest panted like a forge bellows
his eyes were full of the ignoble happiness of a feeble cruel and cowardly creature which finds that it can at last harass what it had feared and insult what it has flattered the joy of a dwarf who should be able to set his heel on the head of goliath the joy of a jackal which is beginning to renew sick bulk so nearly dead that he can no longer defend himself but sufficiently alive to suffer still
m
leblanc did not interrupt him but said to him when he paused i do not know what you mean to say
